main event: Several airmen reported sightings of a shiny aluminum circular object in Seattle, Washington on August 22, 1949.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be 75 to 100 feet in diameter with an estimated depth of 10 to 15 feet.,The object was reported to travel at speeds estimated between 500 to 600 miles per hour.,Witnesses described the object's sound as similar to that of a jet aircraft.,The object did not show any signs of maneuverability and traveled straight.,Multiple witnesses from the 143rd National Guard reported similar sightings around the same time.
witness description: airmen from the 143rd National Guard Aircraft Control and Warning Squadron and Seattle Air Route Traffic Controllers
